// Agent0 — MCP recipes (specs 012 + 025)
//
// This file is a TEMPLATE. Workflow:
//   1. cp .mcp.json.example .mcp.json
//   2. Open .mcp.json and REMOVE the leading `//` markers from the blocks
//      you want active.
//   3. JSON does NOT support `//` comments. Strict parsers reject them.
//      The `.example` suffix is the "do not parse directly" signal; the
//      copy step in (1) is where you make the file valid JSON.
//   4. For DBHub: set DATABASE_URL in your shell or .env before launching
//      claude. NEVER commit a populated DATABASE_URL to git.
//   5. For Chrome DevTools MCP: confirm Chrome/Chrome-for-Testing is
//      installed on the host (`which google-chrome`).
//   6. For product-pipeline (spec 025): runs locally from this repo's
//      packages/ subtree — only works WITHIN the Agent0 repo (or a fork
//      that has cloned packages/mcp-product-pipeline/). Forks without
//      packages/ wait for the v2 npm publish. Full activation docs:
//      packages/mcp-product-pipeline/README.md
//   7. Restart the Claude Code session — .mcp.json is loaded at start.
//
// Full per-recipe documentation (capabilities, when to enable, runtime
// requirements, security): .claude/rules/mcp-recipes.md (external MCPs)
// and packages/mcp-product-pipeline/README.md (in-repo MCP).
